Arya/Edric Dayne, Regency AU  (this is a side story to my wip a...
body:
for rarepairs week over at @asoiafrarepairs

day 7: free day!

Arya/Edric Dayne, Regency AU

(this is a side story to my wip a lady’s justice (sansa/willas), but i’ve included notes so you should not need to read that to read this.) 

He got used to keeping his curtains closed at night because she appeared whenever she pleased, moving quietly enough that he had little warning. The locks were always undisturbed, and whenever he asked how she entered or exited, she only smiled. “Guess,” she said, but he didn’t know where to begin.

There were moments when it was easy to forget all that loomed ahead — moments it seemed like she’d forgotten for a moment, too. But these acts of rebellion were small, in the grand scheme of things. She sampled spirits from his liquor cabinet, things that ladies weren’t supposed to touch, and liked most of them. He tried to teach her to smoke cigars, which she deemed disgusting. And sometimes they went, disguised, to gambling halls, and she would make a tidy sum playing at cards.

More often there was an anger that simmered deep within her, in danger of boiling over.

Reality was, she was engaged to another.

Read on AO3

summary: If someone has seen my “Arya is a Hufflepuff” post, Also take in mind, that i have always believed that Hogwart House sortings...
body:
If someone has seen my “Arya is a Hufflepuff” post,

Also take in mind, that i have always believed that Hogwart House sortings have never been about who you are or what you need to be, but about what you want to be or about the values or qualities you admire or aspire to have.

  • Harry: yes he is cunning, and “has a zest to prove himself”, but he doesnt admire these qualities. He doesn’t admire or prioritise ambition or cunning, nor self-preservation, he doesn’t view them as important. Bravery, however, is an important trait for him, cause he has seen what cowards are like (Dudley, who used his muscles and his buddies to beat down anyone lower or smaller than him but cant face anyone his equal). Courage is also important to him, cause he never has had anyone have the courage to stand up for him. He wants to have these qualities because no one else does around him does (in Privet Drive and in his muggle life), and he also looks for these qualities in the people around him as well. He values the courage that is needed when standing up to others, the daring needed to fight for what is right.
  • Neville is also similar. No, He isn’t brave but he wants to be brave, he wants to have the courage to stand up for himself. Thus, even though he thought he belonged in Hufflepuff, it was the Gryffindor qualities he admired and aspired to have. 
  • Hermione, who while being very intelligent and wise, prioritised bravery more, hence “Books! And cleverness! There are more important things – friendship and bravery”, same with Professor McGonagall. 
  • Cedric was very brave but he valued fair play and justice as more important and saw them as the traits he wanted to follow and have. 
  • Luna was also brave, she was fair too, but she valued creativity, originality and acceptance and encouraged these qualities in herself and in others. 
  • Peter Pettigrew, he wasn’t brave at all but he was Gryffindor cause he wanted to be brave, and thats what he seeked in his friends cause he couldn’t find it in himself. 

In the same way, Arya is cunning, and resourceful (Slytherin), she is very brave and courageous (Gryffindor), creative and wise and not afraid to be an individual (Ravenclaw), but thats who she is, not what she aspires to be. They are a part of her, but she doesn’t actively seek these traits to define her. For her, being fair is more important, justice and loyalty are more important. These are the qualities she does her best to practice, that she values in life and in her friends. Thats why it doesn’t matter to her that Hotpie and Lommy weren’t brave, or that Gendry wasnt cunning (he was, just not as much as her). They were loyal to her and they were willing to work hard and bear through alongside her (when they were trying to escape Amory Lorch’s men) despite complaining about it. Yes, she values bravery too, but for her being brave means being able to help others, having the courage to stand up to injustice, having the courage to protect others when they cant do it themselves. Its only a tool to serve the qualities that she truly does value.
